I’m Harriet, I’m 22 years old and I live in England, UK.

summary: The Hidden Link Between Farm Antibiotics and Human Illness
title: The Hidden Link Between Farm Antibiotics and Human Illness
excerpt: Antibiotics fed to farm animals transferred super bacteria to humans. We've routinely fed antibiotics to the animals we eat and it’s been clear that those antibiotic doses have been creating drug-resistant bacteria that pass from meat animals to make humans sick.
